<section xml:id="sec-Pythagorean-relationships" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Pythagorean-relationships</title>

  <p> 
    <activity>
    <p><alert>Work in groups</alert></p>
    <p>
      <em>Requirements:</em>
    </p>
    <p>
      A ladder or a long stick.
    </p>
    <p>
     A metre rule 
    </p>  
<em>Procedure:</em>
          <p>
            Measure the length of the ladder.
          </p>
          </li>
          <li>
          <p>
            Lean a ladder against a wall of a building.
          </p>
          </li>
          <li>
          <p>
            Name the side of the triangle formed by the ladder, the wall and the ground.
          </p>
          </li>
          </li>
          <li>
          <p>
            Measure the the vertical height, <em>h.</em>
          </p>
          </li>
          <li>
          <p>
            Measure the length <em>b.</em>
          </p>
          </li>
          <li>
          <p>
            Change the position of the ladder on the wall and the ground several times and measure the length of <em>h</em> and <em>b.</em>
          </p>
          </li>
          <li>
          <p>
            Draw the different right-angle triangle formed by the ladder.
          </p>
          </li>
          <li>
          <p>
            Identify the size of the triangles you have drawn.
          </p>
    </activity>
   
  </p>

</section>